      "writtenOn": "2021-04-07T06:45:18Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "It\u0027s a random number, and I haven\u0027t been able to find a good way of finding the number yet.\n\nI haven\u0027t measured how much memory each upload task consumes, but it\u0027s the total memory cost of pb.Artifact{} + uploadTask{} + the internal storage inside the dispatcher. The size of pb.Artifact{} could be as high as a few KB, if it contains Artifact_Contents{}.\n\nLet\u0027s assume that each task consumes 256 bytes of memory, holding 8000 of tasks in memory costs around 2MB of memory. Maybe, that\u0027s too small to block the clients and slow down the test frameworks? WDYT?",
