      "writtenOn": "2021-04-07T06:45:18Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "It\u0027s mainly because I didn\u0027t find benefits of keeping them separately.\n\n1) none of u.Upload(), u.UploadFromFile(), and u.newRequest() would be used anywhere else. They would exist primarily for readability.\n2) I found that they similar enough to be merged to one function, after removal of lines from L106 to L117 in u.UploadFromFile().\n3) They would have be renamed to u.newHTTPRequest(), u.streamUploadFromFile(), u.streamUploadWithContents() to clearly distinguish them from u.batchUpload() and its helper functions, but I feel the names are too verbose.\n\nOverall, I felt that it\u0027d be easy to look through artifact_uploader.go if I merge them when u.batchUpload() is implemented in artifact_uploader.go. Maybe, I\u0027m biased. LMK if you have different opinions.",
