      "writtenOn": "2021-04-07T06:45:18Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "\u003e\u003e Consider using it only there, while the rest of code (L66, L71) uses less-specific `body`.\nGood point. Thanks. Done.\n\n\u003e\u003e Did you consider a simple rule that if someone passes content in t.art.Content, then use Batch upload?\nIt\u0027s still possible that a test framework uploads an Artifact with Content \u003e 10MB, which has to be uploaded with this function, StreamUpload().\n\nWe can (and probably should) put a limit on the maximum size of art.Content in the proto doc, but I\u0027d still prefer to keep streamUpload() capable of handling both artifact_Content{} and artifact_File{}. Otherwise, I\u0027d have to put the following panic().\n\n```\nfunc StreamUpload(...) {\n  if t.art.GetFilePath() \u003d\u003d \"\" {\n     panic(\"StreamUpload() only accepts artifacts with files. Please fix\")\n  }\n}\n```\n\nI will also have to add inline comments for the panic somewhere. I think the current code is better?",
